DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260415T120000
DTSTAMP:20260328T084043Z
UID:1ef55b80c01657b5b787673aabf4e099@family-events-agent
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:children,play,toddler,museum,family
DESCRIPTION:Organizer: Pretend City Children's Museum - Events\\nAges: 0-6
 0 months\\nCategory: Play & Games\\n\\nPretend City Children’s Museum an
 d Parentis Foundation are partnering for something truly magical at We Re
 ad Wednesdays\, where Littles and Grans read together! Our wonderful Emp
 owering Readers OC reading mentors are bringing the joy of storytelling in
 to the playful world of Pretend City\, where imagination comes alive and e
 very corner invites discovery.\nThis partnership is so important because i
 t introduces children to the love of books in a way that feels fun\, welco
 ming\, and shared. When young learners and older adult mentors gather in a
  place built for wonder\, stories become more than words on a page. They b
 ecome moments of connection\, confidence\, and inspiration across generati
 ons.\nTogether\, Pretend City and Empowering Readers OC are creating a com
 munity where reading is joyful and every story sparks a love of reading.\
 n\nTIME: 11am &#8211\; 12pm\nAbout the Play Partner:\nEmpowering Readers O
 C\, a program of Parentis Foundation\, provides evidence-based literacy in
 tervention and intergenerational mentoring to students in grades 1–5 who
  are reading below grade level. By pairing trained older adult volunteers 
 with students\, the program builds strong reading skills\, confidence\, an
 d a foundation for lifelong learning.\\n\\nMore info: https://www.pretendc
 ity.org/events/we-read-wednesdays-with-empowering-readers-oc/
LOCATION:Pretend City Children's Museum - Events\, 29 Hubble\, Irvine\, CA
 \, 92618
URL:https://www.pretendcity.org/events/we-read-wednesdays-with-empowering-
 readers-oc/
